### Design decisions worth noting

| Concern | Decision |
|---|---|
| **Logging safety** | Every `logger.*` call is wrapped in its own `try/except Exception: pass` so a malformed format argument or a broken handler can never propagate and alter the function's observable behaviour. |
| **CC masking** | `_mask_cc` shows only the last four digits (`****-****-****-1111`). It is called at both `DEBUG` and `INFO` levels — the raw number is never passed to the logger. |
| **Email masking** | `_mask_email` exposes only the first character of the local part (`u***@example.com`). Applied at **all** log levels, not just DEBUG. |
| **SMTP password** | `SMTP_PASS` is referenced only in `server.login()`; it never appears in any log call. `SMTP_USER` (the username) is logged because it is not a secret. |
| **Unknown coupon** | Logged at `WARNING` — it is a valid but unusual situation, matching the original `pass` comment. |
| **Missing email** | Logged at `WARNING` because an order without a notification address is unusual but not an error. |
| **Email send failure** | The caught exception object is logged at `WARNING` (with `%r` so its `repr()` is recorded) before the original `pass` continues, preserving the "email failure is not critical" contract exactly. |
| **Log levels summary** | `DEBUG` = flow tracing / internal state; `INFO` = business milestones (order started, coupon applied, payment OK, email sent); `WARNING` = valid but unusual (unknown coupon, missing email, email failure); `ERROR` = validation failures and payment errors that raise exceptions. |

